<topic id="working-with-databases">
  <title>Working with Databases</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>Databases</indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>XML is a storage and interchange format for structured data and is supported by all major
      database systems. <ph keyref="product"/> offers the means for managing the interaction with
      some of the most commonly used databases (both <i>Relational</i> and <i>Native
        XML</i> databases). Through this interaction, <ph keyref="product"/> helps users with
      browsing, content editing, importing from databases, using XQuery with databases, SQL
      execution, and generating XML Schema from a database structure.</p>
    <p>The types of connections that are supported in <ph keyref="product"/> include:<ul>
        <li><xref href="ibm-db2-connection.dita#ibm-db2-connection">IBM DB2</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="ms-sql-server-connection.dita#ms-sql-server-connection">Microsoft SQL
            Server</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="oracle-xml-db-connection.dita#oracle-xml-db-connection">Oracle
            Database</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="postgresql-connection.dita#postgresql-connection">PostgreSQL</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="berkeley-db-connection.dita#berkeley-db-connection">Berkeley DB
          XML</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="exist-connection.dita#exist-connection">eXist</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="marklogic-connection.dita#marklogic-connection">MarkLogic</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="documentum-connection.dita#documentum-connection">Documentum xDB
            (X-Hive/DB)</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="mysql-database-connection.dita#mysql-database-connection">MySQL</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="generic-database-connection.dita#generic-database-connection">Generic
            JDBC</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="jdbc-odbc-database-connection.dita#jdbc-odbc-database-connection"
            >JDBC-ODBC</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="basex-support.dita#basex-support">BaseX</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="webdav-connection.dita#webdav-connection">WebDAV</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="sharepoint-connection.dita#sharepoint-connection">Microsoft
            SharePoint</xref></li>
      </ul></p>
